channel.title: How do I make my client un-leechable?
channel.description:
How do I make my client un-leechable like Dds-specz or PvP Planet?
like this; [img]http://i582.photobucket.com/albums/ss270/costom_nerd/moparscapepic.jpg[/img]
So no files that they can change client name or ip etc?

item.title: How do I make my client un-leechable?
item.dc:creator: @mad_moparscapian mad_moparscapian
item.description:
@mad_moparscapian wrote:

[quote=“wolfs goal, post:3, topic:271400”][quote author=mad_moparscapian link=topic=358146.msg2735017#msg2735017 date=1239006685]
One way is to compile it and then delete all teh java files and just keep teh class file.s becuase unless people have a good decompiler they cant edit it anyway
[/quote]

That’s true, i always do that. This way noobs don’t leech my models.[/quote]

See i’m not just a pretty face

I have included a pic of me below…
